    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1862-12-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1862-12-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="243" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Burlingame</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 22.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1862-12-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 9, 1862.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of August 23 (No. 24,) has
                            been received, and it affords the President much satisfaction to know
                            that you have been successful in reaching Pekin, and that your residence
                            there begins under favorable auspices.</p>
                <p>Your proceedings at Pekin, as reported, are approved.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Anson Burlingame</hi>, Esh., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
